content.text: Calculate the volume of container A and container B, and the amount of water left, given: Vol. of container A = 30 x 15 x 16 = 7200 ml. Vol. of container B = 10 x 10 x 10 = 1000 ml. Amount of water left = 7200 - 1000 = 6200 ml.
content.text_latex: Calculate the volume of container A and container B, and the amount of water left, given: Vol. of container A = $30 \times 15 \times 16 = 7200$ ml. Vol. of container B = $10 \times 10 \times 10 = 1000$ ml. Amt. of water left = $7200 - 1000 = 6200$ ml.
